5. Evolution of Money
5.1 Barter System
•	Direct exchange of commodity for commodity
5.2 Copper Coins
•	Making cost increases
•	Value decreases
5.3 Gold
•	Treated as an asset
•	Tax is applicable
5.4 Paper Money
•	Printing increases
•	Population increases
•	Accountability decreases
•	Leads to high inflation
5.5 Banking System
•	Credit cards
•	Debit cards
5.6 E-Money
•	Google Pay
•	PhonePe
•	UPI
•	Secured through OTP
•	Fiat currency includes INR and e-Rupee
5.7 Cryptocurrency
•	Based on Decentralized Finance (DeFi)
