12. Blockchain
Blockchain is a shared, immutable ledger that records transactions and tracks assets in business networks.
Advantages of Blockchain
•	Security
•	No middleman
•	Immutability
•	Transparency
•	No duplication
13. Centralized System (Web 2.0)
Architecture:
Central Server → Internet → Device
Example: WhatsApp
Explanation:
•	Data is stored in a centralized database server
•	All user information is controlled by a single authority
•	User data may be shared or leaked without user awareness
14. Decentralized System (Web 3.0)
Architecture:
Transaction → Block 1 → Block 2 → Block 3
•	Data is stored in a distributed ledger
•	If 1 BTC is transferred in Block 3, all blocks record the transaction
•	Only the current block is encrypted
________________________________________
15. Block Structure
Block 1
•	Hash: 296F
•	Previous Hash: 000
Block 2
•	Hash: 6HQ9
•	Previous Hash: 296F
Block 3
•	Hash: 1G79
•	Previous Hash: 6HQ9
